default• Should the government take any further any specific actions in relation to cooling? 
defaultDistrict cooling might seem more prevalent in warmer countries but by successfully deploying
default “ambient thermal loops” cooling can be part of the heat equation. Without a doubt, burning fuel to heat stuff and burning electricity to cool it back down in an industrial context is poor.
